=head1 NAME

gbatch_varread - read the details of a variable

=head1 SYNOPSIS

=for man
\&\fB#include <gbatch.h>\fR
.PP

=for html
<STRONG>#include &lt;gbatch.h&gt;</STRONG>
<br>

B<int gbatch_varread(const int>
I<fd>B<, const unsigned>
I<flags>B<, const slotno_t>
I<slot>B<, apiBtvar *>I<vard>B<)>

=head1 DESCRIPTION

The function B<gbatch_varread> is used to read the details for a variable

I<fd> is a file descriptor which was previously returned by a
successful call to gbatch_open(3).

I<flags> is zero or C<GBATCH_FLAG_IGNORESEQ> to ignore recent changes
to the variable list.

I<slot> is the slot number corresponding to the variable as returned
by gbatch_varlist(3) or xb_varfind(3).

I<vard> is a pointer to a structure which will contain the details of
the variable.

=head1 RETURN VALUES

The function returns 0 if successful, otherwise an error code as
defined in the include file \fBgbatch.h\fR.

